snippet.title: NiKOs FIRST TIME in a BALL PIT! ultimate indoor park with our daredevil kids! (family night routine)
snippet.description:
Adley and Niko have the BEST NIGHT EVER at our new favorite place!!

JOIN OUR FAM!! --- http://goo.gl/rfgp8V

Best Ball Pit Day Ever 1015

We were not ready for this!! I got home from the spacestation and Jenny said she found this new place not far from us that was a brand new indoor park. It sounded really fun and it would be some great family fun. But this place was even better than we thought. As soon as we got there, Adley was wanting to run and play, she could hardly contain her excitement (and honestly, I felt the same way)!

We climbed all over his super fun playground toy, with slides and balance bridges, we found trampolines that we did tricks on and one that you could jump on a huge air blob you could jump on. The was a balance beam over a foam pit that Adley and I did tricks on and we found the ultimate ball pit, and it was Niko's first time in one. At first he didn't really seem to understand, but then he started having tons of fun. So cute watching the kids just run all over the place, with some many fun things to do. Adley is a little daredevil, she has no fear! They have an obstacle course machine on some trampolines and Adley does amazing at it!!

They also have a sky coaster track that Jenny and I took turns riding on. Adley was just a little to short to ride, but she had fun watching her mom and dad zip around the ceiling. We had so much fun and as we were getting ready to leave, we found even more things for us to do. We're definitely going to come back! 

Everyone really needs to check this place out. This isn't a brand deal or a partnership, me and my family genuinely had so much fun that I wanted to give them a shout out and thank them for the amazing time!!

Urban Air Trampoline and Adventure Park -- http://www.urbanairtrampolinepark.com/locations/Utah/Clearfield

When we get home the kids are literally exhausted and go straight to bed (maybe a new bed time routine lol). So Jenny and I eat some dinner and have a little catch up session with you guys cause it's been a while since we had a real talk and we've missed you guys!

snippet.description:
David and his brothers had a family fun playtime with indoor Playground Play Area for Kids! This Play Area for children had giant slides, kids can slide, jump, climb on the playground. There's even a toddler play center with toys and ball pits. There's also plasma cars racing kids can ride. Great video for Kids who loves to have fun playing. Subscribe for more Family fun time:https://goo.gl/SDhNuj

The boys get to burn off some excess energy in this video taken at Zippy Zoom Indoor Playground in Welland, Ontario. http://zippyzoomplayground.com/

The facility is 8000 sq ft and includes several slides,  tons of plasma cars, a ball pit, ball blasters, a ball fountain machine, a spinner seat, a waterbed/trampoline and fully padded floors.  The facility is well built with all the kids safety in mind.  Even the parents can follow the little ones into the playground and get a workout themselves.  We've seen adults try and enjoy the plasma cars in the facility as well!

Their prices are very reasonable and if the kiddies enjoy themselves a lot, then we suggest getting a monthly membership or even a yearly.  This is a sure cure for those winter blues when outdoor playground activities are not possible due to weather.  Zippy Zoom also has a small snack bar for snacks and drinks but if that is not enough, they also allow Domino's pizza to deliver.  The facility has enough space for seating while dining and reading as well if that is your preference.  Most importantly, the facility has washrooms onsite for those emergencies that all families with small kids know!

Overall, the trip to Zippy Zoom in Welland, Ontario is well worth the drive!  The kids get to burn off their energy (they slept very well that night!), Dad get to follow along and get some exercise as well and everybody had fun no matter what the weather is outside!  

Check them out and you might see us there because we are planning on making another visit!

WHAT IS KIDCITY?
Kidcity is a children's museum with three floors of imagination play, where kids ages 1 to 7 play pretend with their favorite grown-ups.   Our exhibits are handmade and one-of-a-kind, built by in-house artists who love inspiring playfulness in visitors of all ages.

"About Children's Museums
Why Visit a Children’s Museum?

Riding on train rides and race cars with Chucky in the passenger seat, it was an exciting day for these kids on their first time ever to a place like Chucky Cheese.  There was an indoor playground with a crawl tube and some slides, lots of fun arcade games to play and cool rides for the kids. 

Most people have taken their kids to Chuckee Cheese before and know how much fun it is for kids.  There is so much noise and fun games going on with the puppets and crazy animatronic characters, my favorite was the rock band that came out and started playing music.  

Gathering tickets was a new experience for the kids, as they learned how to earn them from winning games and arcade games, while being able to pick out colorful gifts and surprises at the end of their trip to Chuckee CHeeses.  Lots of opportunity for family fun in the indoor play area and arcade!

snippet.title: How sisters play in an Indoor Playground
snippet.description:
Indoor Playground can be a good option to play when the outside weather is not kids friendly.
Kids can have a lot of fun without spending a large budget to visit a faraway theme park.

Go to the google map, and search the nearby "Indoor Playground", you will be amazed about the number of options. Most of them are economic, some even provide membership for frequent visitors. Some also provide extra-curriculum classes inside of it.

Have fun!


Youtube Channel "Sisters Fun" is where Emma and Ella share their fun.
